STEPS TO INSTALL & RUN RABBITMQ:

I - Installing Erlang

1. Download Erlang Programming Language: Source File (65.0 MB) 

	http://www.erlang.org/download.html

2. Follow The Warrior Method:

	http://www.erlang.org/doc/installation_guide/INSTALL.html

	Tested in unbuntu, should work for OS X ( only the building method that change)

	Ensure that An Erlang runtime system is started with command erl

II - Installing RabbitMQ

Follow https://www.rabbitmq.com/download.html

You should be able to launch RabbitMQ server with rabbitmq-server script

STEPS TO INSTALL & RUN MONGODB

1- Follow the full guide : https://docs.mongodb.org/v3.0/administration/install-on-linux/
			   https://docs.mongodb.org/v3.0/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-os-x/

( I used the default config of the guide )

2- You should be able to launch the DB server with the command line : mongod
   (Mongodb needs write permission on /data/db ensure that)

3- To find or query data use mongo shell : mongo

4- Install mongodb module : npm install mongodb
   This module install kerboros module implicitly if there is errors, install the Kerberos Development Package: sudo apt-get install libkrb5-dev
   and ignore npm errors

